column5: Water was dirty, 61.5 degrees and fishing was slow, tried swimbaits, spinnerbaits, crankbaits, drop shot and then we caught 4 Smallies on tubes 2 lbs maybe, Darcy felt something set the hook and foul hooked a gizzard shad in the back fin some how, drifting in the faster outflow & Darcy's rod jumped, set the hook, says fish on get the net it's a good one & as I turned around I see this 24" 5.5lb Rainbow on a Chompers Tube sprayed with Garlic, a real nice end to his season he doesn't think he'll get out again, I'm heading back out today, see what we can catch.
thats awesome.. Love it when that happens eh
